v 3
d catllm: classify, summarize, and discover themes in text with LLMs
d
d catllm wraps the cat-stack Python package so Stata users can classify
d open-ended text, summarize it, and discover category schemes from it
d using large language models. Works with OpenAI, Anthropic, Google,
d Mistral, Perplexity, xAI, HuggingFace, and local Ollama models. The
d domain() option selects prompt templates tuned for political,
d sentiment, academic, survey, cognitive, or web text.
d
d Requires: Stata 16+ with Python integration, Python 3.8+, cat-stack >= 1.6.0
d
d Author: Christopher Soria
d Support: chrissoria@berkeley.edu
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260603

